    "body": "Previously, when an invalid port was specified in `-rpcbind`, `SplitHostPort()` return was ignored and attempt would be made to bind to the default rpcbind port (with the host/port treated as a host).\r\n\r\nThis updates `HTTPBindAddresses()` to handle the invalid port before attempting the bind.\r\n\r\nAlso adds associated functional tests.",
